<HEADLINE>
<P>
POWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jesse Jackson (Op-Ed Page column, Jan. 4) and Charlton Heston (letter, Jan. 12) 
are both wrong. 
</P>
<P>
What guns "create" is power. This may be used for good or evil. It may lead to 
democracy, but it may create totalitarianism, institutionalized racism, 
theocracy -- you name it. 
</P>
<P>
As Gandhi demonstrated, when people are ready for freedom, their moral force is 
more effective than guns. He was, obviously, the man of the century. 
</P>
<P>
JUDITH L. BARNEY 
</P>
<P>
Solana Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
