<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Webber to Produce Show at Disney World: Composer Andrew Lloyd Webber will move 
on from cats to all other kinds of animals, as the executive producer of a new 
show at Disney World in Orlando, Fla., called "Noah's Ark." 
</P>
<P>
Lloyd Webber, the creator of "Cats" and "Phantom of the Opera," will compose an 
original symphonic score for the pageant, which will be staged on water. "This 
is the most ambitious night-time spectacle in Disney history," said Michael 
Eisner, chairman and chief executive officer of the Walt Disney Co. Set to open 
in 1992, "Noah's Ark" will be part of 29 new shows that Disney plans to add to 
its Florida park in the 1990s. Claudia Puig 
</P>
