<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING CREW FLEES BOAT ABLAZE OFF PALOS VERDES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coast Guard personnel took more than six hours to control a fire that broke out 
Sunday morning on a fishing trawler 18 miles south of the Palos Verdes 
Peninsula, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Ten crew members abandoned the "Luck Seven" and drifted in two life rafts for 
about 30 minutes before they were picked up by a passing fishing boat, Coast 
Guard Lt. John Dagostino said. 
</P>
<P>
The 96-foot trawler was carrying eels packed in peat moss, Dagostino said. 
</P>
<P>
The amount of damage done to the boat and the cause of the fire was not 
immediately determined, the lieutenant said. Authorities did not identify the 
boat's owner. 
</P>
