<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEREZ TO DEFEND TITLE TONIGHT AT FORUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Raul Perez makes the fourth defense of his World Boxing Council bantamweight 
championship at the Forum tonight against ninth-ranked Gaby Canizales, a former 
champion. 
</P>
<P>
Perez, 5 feet 11 inches, from Tijuana, is one of the tallest bantamweight 
champions and is a textbook boxer. He will have a major height advantage over 
the 5-5 1/2 Canizales, an aggressive fighter from Laredo, Tex. This is the 
first of a planned 12 world title fights at the Forum this year. 
</P>
<P>
Perez, who earned the bantamweight title by beating Miguel Lora in Las Vegas in 
1988, is 44-1. Canizales, briefly the World Boxing Assn. champion in 1986, is 
45-6. 
</P>
