<P>
MICHIGAN STATE'S PERLES SAYS HE IS NEGOTIATING CONTRACT WITH JETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICH CIMINI, NEWSDAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Michigan State Coach George Perles apparently has been offered the Jets' 
coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
The 55-year-old Perles told a Pittsburgh television station Sunday that he's in 
the process of negotiating a contract with the Jets. 
</P>
<P>
"When you're talking to people and you're negotiating, you certainly try to 
keep as much of it to yourself as you can," Perles told WPXI-TV, Pittsburgh's 
NBC affiliate, in a brief interview at the airport. "I don't feel comfortable 
negotiating in front of the cameras. I've got some work to do on this." 
</P>
<P>
Perles, accompanied by an assistant coach, was in Pittsburgh to recruit players 
in the area. 
</P>
<P>
Jet General Manager Dick Steinberg, at the Senior Bowl Saturday, said he would 
have an announcement "real soon." 
</P>
<P>
One possible holdup is Perles' status at Michigan State. Perles is a strong 
candidate to become the athletic director. 
</P>
