<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN, 66, DIES WHEN CAR HITS TREE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 66-year-old Orange woman was killed Sunday afternoon when she lost control of 
her car and rammed into a tree, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Pauline Evelynn Jauregui was pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
She was driving east on Michaelson Drive in Irvine when she lost control of her 
car, police said. They said the car jumped a curb and traveled 380 feet before 
hitting the tree, near Elm Tree Lane in front of the Village Park Recreation 
Center. Police estimated her speed at 55 to 60 m.p.h. The area has a speed 
limit of 35. 
</P>
</TEXT>
