<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; 
</P>
<P>
ARTS SERIES PLANNED FOR SCHOOLCHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thousands of schoolchildren in the Saddleback Valley are expected to 
participate in the annual Mission Viejo Arts for Youth series this month. 
</P>
<P>
The program will bring local performing artists onto school campuses throughout 
the area as well as sending students to concert and dance venues in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Viejo and Aliso Viejo elementary schoolchildren in kindergarten through 
the third grade will see "Rumpelstiltskin" performed by the Lilliput players. 
Students in higher grades will experience a variety of dances by several area 
dance companies. 
</P>
<P>
Junior high school students will hear a jazz concert by the Bobby Medina Jazz 
Quintet, and high school students are scheduled to attend a performance of "A 
Mid-Summer Night's Dream" at the South Coast Repertory Theatre. 
</P>
<P>
Sixth-grade students will attend the Los Angeles Ballet Theater's performance 
of "The Little Prince" at the Orange County Performing Arts Center. 
</P>
<P>
The arts program will conclude March 20 with Mission Viejo's spring concert, 
featuring choirs from three high schools and the Saddleback College symphony 
and chorus. 
</P>
<P>
Ticket proceeds from the evening concert will be donated to music programs in 
the Saddleback Valley school districts. 
</P>
<P>
The arts program, sponsored by the Mission Viejo Co., is in its fourth year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
