<TEXT>
<P>
Britain's Princess Anne denied banner-headline reports today that she was 
planning to divorce her estranged husband, Mark Phillips. 
</P>
<P>
"I haven't seen a paper today," Queen Elizabeth's only daughter told 
Independent Television News. "Divorce? Never been mentioned by anybody." 
</P>
<P>
The 39-year-old Princess Royal, looking puzzled, was speaking from behind the 
wheel of a farm vehicle on her country estate in western England. 
</P>
<P>
Princess Anne and Phillips announced their separation last August, saying there 
were no plans for divorce proceedings. 
</P>
<P>
In a report headlined "Anne: I Want a Quickie Divorce," the Daily Express said 
the princess was pushing to end the 15-year-old marriage despite Phillips' wish 
to let the separation run on indefinitely. 
