</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRANKFURT, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chrysler Corp. and Austrian auto maker Steyr-Daimler-Puch AG said today that 
they will establish a joint venture for producing Chrysler's popular mini-vans 
in Austria. 
</P>
<P>
The agreement in principle between Chrysler and the Austrian engineering and 
automotive company provides for establishment of joint production of the 
Chrysler Voyager in Graz, Austria's second-largest city, for the European 
market. 
</P>
<P>
Under the joint venture, Chrysler and Steyr-Daimler-Puch Fahrzeugtechnick GMBH 
will develop Voyager spare parts specifically designed for the European market, 
Chrysler Chairman Lee Iacocca said at a news conference in Vienna. 
</P>
<P>
Iacocca said production will begin in the spring of 1991. 
