<P>
MCA EXPECTS TO SHOW PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Universal City-based MCA Inc., the film maker and distributor whose earnings 
have been boosted by a series of hits, said today it will take $53 million in 
charges against 1989 earnings but expects to post higher profits. 
</P>
<P>
MCA's Universal Pictures has produced recent box office hits like "Sea of 
Love," "Parenthood," "Do the Right Thing," "Back to the Future II" and "Born on 
the Fourth of July." 
</P>
<P>
MCA also runs the Universal Studios theme park in Los Angeles and expects to 
open another in Orlando later this year. 
</P>
<P>
The company said it will sell its LJN Toys Ltd. unit and take a $30-million 
charge against 1989 earnings for the sale. MCA also said it would take a 
$23-million write-off for discontinued operations. 
</P>
<P>
The company said that despite losses from LJN, it expects to report higher 
earnings for 1989. 
</P>
<P>
In 1988, MCA earned $164.9 million, or $2.26 per share. 
</P>
<P>
In early trading, MCA share prices were down 12.5 cents to $57.625. 
</P>
</TEXT>
