<P>
SEATTLE SUBS FARMER FOR ELLIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Seattle SuperSonics signed veteran shooting guard Jim Farmer to replace 
Dale Ellis, who is recuperating from injuries suffered in a car crash. 
</P>
<P>
Farmer, a first-round draft choice of the Dallas Mavericks in the 1987 NBA 
draft from University of Alabama, averaged 3.2 points in 67 games -- 30 with 
Dallas in 1987-88 and 37 with Utah in 1988-89. 
</P>
<P>
Farmer, signed Sunday, was to practice with the Sonics today. 
</P>
