<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
LOUISIANA TECH WOMEN TOP POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Louisiana Tech (14-0), Stanford (15-0), Tennessee (13-3) and UNLV (16-1), the 
top four teams in the Associated Press women's basketball poll, avoided upsets 
that struck others in the rankings and held their positions in the weekly 
balloting, announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Top-ranked Louisiana Tech received 53 first-place votes and 1,613 points from a 
nationwide panel of 65 women's coaches. No. 2 Stanford, which ripped through 
UCLA and Southern Cal for two Pac-10 road victories, received the other 12 
first-place votes and 1,572 points. 
</P>
<P>
They were followed in the top 10 by Tennessee, UNLV, Texas (11-3), Long Beach 
State (11-3), Georgia (14-2), Washington (14-2), Stephen F. Austin (13-1) and 
Purdue (12-3). 
</P>
</TEXT>
